---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import RelatedServices from '../../components/RelatedServices.astro';
import ServiceAreasLink from '../../components/ServiceAreasLink.astro';
import { SITE_CONFIG } from '../../config';
import { generateServiceSchema } from '../../utils/schema';

const serviceSchema = generateServiceSchema('driveways', 'Professional concrete driveway installation and repair services in Deptford, NJ. Residential and commercial driveways with free estimates.');
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Concrete Driveway Installation & Repair in Deptford, NJ"
  description="Expert concrete driveway contractors in Deptford, NJ. New driveway installation, repairs, resurfacing, and decorative options. Serving Gloucester County with quality concrete driveways."
  schema={serviceSchema}
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Concrete Driveway Installation & Repair in Deptford, New Jersey</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Professional driveway installation and repair services for residential and commercial properties. Free estimates on all driveway projects.</p>
      <a href="#contact-form" class="cta-primary">Get Free Driveway Estimate</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Expert Driveway Services</h2>
      <p>We provide professional concrete driveway installation and repair services throughout Deptford and surrounding areas. Our durable driveways enhance curb appeal and provide years of reliable service.</p>

      <h3>Driveway Services</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>New driveway installation</li>
        <li>Driveway repair and resurfacing</li>
        <li>Driveway replacement</li>
        <li>Decorative concrete driveways</li>
        <li>Driveway expansion</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>What's Included in Our Driveway Service</h3>
      <p>When you choose Deptford Concrete Contractors for your driveway project, you receive complete service from consultation to completion:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Free On-Site Estimate:</strong> We visit your property to assess your current driveway or installation site, discuss your needs, and provide a detailed written estimate</li>
        <li><strong>Site Preparation:</strong> Proper excavation, grading, and base preparation to ensure your driveway lasts</li>
        <li><strong>Quality Materials:</strong> High-grade concrete mixes specifically designed for New Jersey's freeze-thaw climate</li>
        <li><strong>Professional Installation:</strong> Expert installation by experienced concrete professionals with attention to detail</li>
        <li><strong>Proper Drainage:</strong> Correct slope and drainage to prevent water damage and ice buildup</li>
        <li><strong>Expansion Joints:</strong> Properly placed expansion joints to prevent cracking from temperature changes</li>
        <li><strong>Finishing Options:</strong> Smooth finish, brushed finish, or decorative options based on your preference</li>
        <li><strong>Cleanup:</strong> Complete site cleanup after installation, leaving your property ready to use</li>
        <li><strong>Maintenance Guidance:</strong> Advice on proper care and maintenance to extend your driveway's lifespan</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Our Driveway Installation Process</h3>
      <p>We follow a proven process to ensure your driveway is installed correctly and efficiently:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Site Evaluation:</strong> We assess your property, existing driveway condition (if applicable), drainage patterns, and local requirements</li>
        <li><strong>Design & Planning:</strong> We create a driveway design that meets your needs, property layout, and local codes</li>
        <li><strong>Permit Assistance:</strong> We help secure necessary permits if required by your municipality</li>
        <li><strong>Excavation & Base Preparation:</strong> Professional excavation and proper base material installation for stability</li>
        <li><strong>Formwork & Reinforcement:</strong> Installation of forms and reinforcement (if needed) for your specific driveway requirements</li>
        <li><strong>Concrete Pouring:</strong> Placement of high-quality concrete mix appropriate for driveway use</li>
        <li><strong>Finishing:</strong> Proper finishing and texturing based on your chosen style</li>
        <li><strong>Curing:</strong> Proper curing time to ensure maximum strength and durability</li>
        <li><strong>Final Inspection:</strong> Quality check to ensure your driveway meets all standards</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Common Driveway Issues We Solve</h3>
      <p>Our driveway services address many common problems homeowners face:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Cracking and Settling:</strong> Old driveways with extensive cracking or settling can be replaced with a new, properly installed concrete driveway</li>
        <li><strong>Poor Drainage:</strong> Driveways that pool water or create ice hazards can be redesigned with proper slope and drainage</li>
        <li><strong>Surface Deterioration:</strong> Driveways with spalling, scaling, or surface damage can be resurfaced or replaced</li>
        <li><strong>Insufficient Size:</strong> Driveways that are too narrow or short can be expanded to meet your current needs</li>
        <li><strong>Outdated Appearance:</strong> Old, plain driveways can be replaced with decorative options like stamped concrete</li>
        <li><strong>Safety Concerns:</strong> Uneven surfaces, trip hazards, or poor visibility can be addressed with professional installation</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Driveway Styles & Options</h3>
      <p>We offer various driveway styles to match your home and preferences:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Standard Concrete Driveways:</strong> Durable, smooth finish perfect for most homes - provides excellent value and longevity</li>
        <li><strong>Stamped Concrete Driveways:</strong> Decorative patterns and textures that mimic stone, brick, or other materials - <a href="/services/stamped-concrete">Learn more about stamped concrete â†’</a></li>
        <li><strong>Colored Concrete:</strong> Custom colors to match your home's aesthetic and enhance curb appeal</li>
        <li><strong>Reinforced Driveways:</strong> Extra durability with rebar reinforcement for heavy vehicles or challenging soil conditions</li>
        <li><strong>Brushed Finish:</strong> Textured surface that provides better traction, especially in wet or icy conditions</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>What Happens When You Call</h3>
      <p>Getting your new driveway or driveway repair is straightforward with our streamlined process:</p>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Initial Contact (24-48 Hour Response):</strong> When you reach out via phone or our contact form, we'll respond within 24-48 hours to schedule your free estimate</li>
        <li><strong>Free On-Site Estimate:</strong> We visit your property to assess your needs, discuss options, and provide a detailed written estimate with no obligation</li>
        <li><strong>Project Planning:</strong> Once you approve the estimate, we handle all planning including permits (if needed), material ordering, and scheduling</li>
        <li><strong>Professional Installation:</strong> Our experienced team completes your driveway installation or repair efficiently and professionally</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Our Customer Service Promise</h3>
      <p>At Deptford Concrete Contractors, we believe in complete transparency and honest communication:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>No Hidden Fees:</strong> Your written estimate includes all costs - materials, labor, permits, and cleanup - no surprises</li>
        <li><strong>Clear Communication:</strong> We keep you informed at every step, from initial estimate through project completion</li>
        <li><strong>Realistic Timelines:</strong> We provide honest timelines based on project scope and weather conditions - typically 1-2 days for most driveways</li>
        <li><strong>Quality Guarantee:</strong> We stand behind our work and ensure your driveway meets all quality and code standards</li>
        <li><strong>Responsive Service:</strong> We respond to questions and concerns promptly, typically within 24-48 hours</li>
        <li><strong>Licensed & Insured:</strong> Full professional coverage protects you and your property throughout the project</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Driveway Investment Factors</h3>
      <p>Understanding what affects your driveway investment helps you make informed decisions. Several factors influence the final cost:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Size and Layout:</strong> Larger driveways or complex layouts require more materials and labor</li>
        <li><strong>Driveway Style:</strong> Standard concrete is most economical, while stamped or colored options add to the investment</li>
        <li><strong>Site Preparation:</strong> Challenging terrain, existing driveway removal, or extensive excavation affects cost</li>
        <li><strong>Reinforcement Needs:</strong> Heavy vehicles or challenging soil may require additional reinforcement</li>
        <li><strong>Drainage Requirements:</strong> Properties with drainage challenges may need additional work</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Difficult access may require special equipment or additional time</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We provide free, detailed estimates that break down all costs so you understand exactly what you're investing in. There are no hidden fees or surprise charges - what we quote is what you pay.</p>

      <h3>Related Services</h3>
      <p>Many homeowners pair driveway installation with other concrete services:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="/services/walkways">Walkway Installation</a> - Connect your driveway to your front door</li>
        <li><a href="/services/patios">Patio Installation</a> - Create outdoor living spaces</li>
        <li><a href="/services/concrete-slabs">Concrete Slab Services</a> - For parking pads or additional concrete surfaces</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Areas We Serve</h3>
      <p>We provide driveway installation and repair services throughout <a href="/locations/deptford-nj">Deptford</a>, <a href="/locations/west-deptford-nj">West Deptford</a>, <a href="/locations/woodbury-nj">Woodbury</a>, <a href="/locations/glassboro-nj">Glassboro</a>, and <a href="/locations">all surrounding Gloucester County communities</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <RelatedServices currentService="driveways" />
  <ServiceAreasLink serviceName="Driveways" />

  <section id="contact-form" class="contact-section">
    <div class="container">
      <ContactForm 
        title="Get Your Free Driveway Estimate"
        service="driveways"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Driveway FAQs</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How long does a concrete driveway last?</h3>
          <p>A properly installed concrete driveway can last 25-30 years or more with proper maintenance. Our driveways are designed for New Jersey's climate and built to withstand freeze-thaw cycles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How long does driveway installation take?</h3>
          <p>Most driveway installations are completed within 1-2 days, depending on size and complexity. We'll provide a detailed timeline during your free estimate.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can you repair an existing driveway instead of replacing it?</h3>
          <p>Yes, we can often repair or resurface existing driveways if the damage is limited. We'll assess your driveway during the free estimate and recommend the best solution.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Do I need a permit for a new driveway?</h3>
          <p>Permit requirements vary by municipality. We'll check local requirements and assist with permit applications if needed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What's the difference between standard and stamped concrete driveways?</h3>
          <p>Standard concrete driveways have a smooth or brushed finish. Stamped concrete driveways feature decorative patterns and textures that mimic stone, brick, or other materials. Stamped options cost more but provide enhanced curb appeal.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

